Validates the current state of the canvas and reports visual issues.

## When to Use

- After generating or editing a diagram, call this tool to verify the visual quality of your changes before presenting the result to the user.
- When the user asks you to check or fix layout issues.
- *ValidateCanvas* runs after mutation tools within the same wave, so you can include it in the same wave as your final mutations — no need to call it in a separate wave.

## Parameters

- **ItemIds** (optional): Specific item IDs to validate. If omitted, validates all blocks and lines in the document.
- **Validators** (optional): The specific validators to run, chosen from the list below. Pass the specific validators you want to run. ALL validators will run by default if undefined or empty. When unsure whether a validator is relevant, include it.

## Validators

${UcLGg.map(a=>`- **${a.type}**: ${a.description}`).join("\n")}

## Output

Returns a list of issues found.

Ensure any reported issues were intentional.  If any issues are not intentional, fix them before ending the execution loop or messaging the user.
